headline: Parnas’s Texts Tie Nunes’s Aide to Ukraine Efforts
abstract: Texts raised more questions about information suggesting that the United States ambassador to Ukraine was under surveillance.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats released another round of information on Friday that raised questions about elements of the impeachment inquiry, including allegations about the surveillance of the United States ambassador in Ukraine and efforts by an aide to a top congressional Republican to pursue investigations sought by President Trump.
keywords: Trump-Ukraine Whistle-blower Complaint and Impeachment Inquiry
